</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3510CEAFFFD0D484387FCAA3DE2FC21" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF45F61FFFD0D484387FCAA3DE2FC21" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis id="B93F8373FFFD0D484387FCAA3F48FC4D" bold="true" box="[199,328,873,899]" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">Etymology</emphasis>
: Dedicated to Mariom A. Carvajal, in recognition of her work on pentatomoid taxonomy, especially in understudied groups such as the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B24E2FFFD0D484170FC4E3D00FC69" box="[560,768,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Acanthosomatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Acanthosomatidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B24E2FFFD0D48407CFC4E3DEEFC69" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1864" box="[828,1006,909,935]" class="Insecta" family="Tessaratomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tessaratomidae</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, the first author, who is her husband, recognizes her support during the realization of his doctoral dissertation. This genus belongs to “New genus 1” in the Faúndez (2017) dissertation. Gender of the genus feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3510CEAFFFD0D484387FC3B3B5FFB09" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF45F61FFFD0D484387FC3B3B5FFB09" blockId="1.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis id="B93F8373FFFD0D484387FC3B3F52FBDD" bold="true" box="[199,338,1016,1043]" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">Comments:</emphasis>
This new genus is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B24E2FFFD0D484040FC3A3DBBFBDD" authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1910" box="[768,955,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hillieria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F8373FFFD0D484040FC3A3D60FBDD" box="[768,864,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">Hillieria</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B24E2FFFD0D4840B6FC3A3B08FBDD" authority="Distant. The" authorityName="Distant. The" authorityYear="1910" box="[1014,1288,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Pseudaelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F8373FFFD0D4840B6FC3A3A72FBDD" box="[1014,1138,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">Pseudaelia</emphasis>
Distant. The
</taxonomicName>
shape of the head, with the open, broad and rounded paraclypei (
<figureCitation id="137043E4FFFD0D48419BFBDE3D29FBF9" box="[731,809,1053,1079]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1465,1490]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,417,1445]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,417,1445]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mariomella singularis gen. et sp. nov. A. Habitus (Scale = 1mm); B. External female genitalia, ventral view (Scale = 1mm); C. Male pygophore, dorsal view (Scale = 0.5 mm); D. Tibia (Scale = 1.5 mm); E. Male paramere lateral view (Scale = 0.1mm); F. Metapleuron (Scale = 0.7mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
) will help distinguish this genus. The head is triangular, apically acute, with contiguous paraclypei in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B24E2FFFD0D4841D8FB823CF1FB95" box="[664,753,1089,1115]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Phytolaccaceae" genus="Hilleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F8373FFFD0D4841D8FB823CF1FB95" box="[664,753,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">Hilleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and subtriangular and broad in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B24E2FFFD0D484722FB823ADEFB95" authorityName="Distant. The" authorityYear="1910" box="[1122,1246,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Pseudaelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93F8373FFFD0D484722FB823ADEFB95" box="[1122,1246,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">Pseudaelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; with paraclypei rounded at level of the anteclypeus, or sometimes contiguous beyond it. The shape of the anterolateral angles of the pronotum, relatively wide and oriented anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="137043E4FFFD0D484196FB4A3D27FB6D" box="[726,807,1161,1187]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1465,1490]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,417,1445]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,417,1445]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mariomella singularis gen. et sp. nov. A. Habitus (Scale = 1mm); B. External female genitalia, ventral view (Scale = 1mm); C. Male pygophore, dorsal view (Scale = 0.5 mm); D. Tibia (Scale = 1.5 mm); E. Male paramere lateral view (Scale = 0.1mm); F. Metapleuron (Scale = 0.7mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
), and the non-sulcate, tubular tibiae (
<figureCitation id="137043E4FFFD0D484790FB4A3B29FB6D" box="[1232,1321,1161,1187]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1465,1490]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,417,1445]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,417,1445]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mariomella singularis gen. et sp. nov. A. Habitus (Scale = 1mm); B. External female genitalia, ventral view (Scale = 1mm); C. Male pygophore, dorsal view (Scale = 0.5 mm); D. Tibia (Scale = 1.5 mm); E. Male paramere lateral view (Scale = 0.1mm); F. Metapleuron (Scale = 0.7mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3373069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="190">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
), separate this genus from both 
<taxonomicName id="4C4B24E2FFFD0D4842C5FB6E3FE5FB09" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1910" box="[389,485,1197,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hillieria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
